'''奇克森特米哈伊·米哈伊'''（{{lang-hu|Csíkszentmihályi Mihály}}， {{IPA-hu|ˈt͡ʃiːksɛntmihaːji ˈmihaːj|pron|Mihály Csíkszentmihályi.ogg}}；{{lang-en|Mihaly Csikszentmihalyi}}，{{IPAc-en|ˈ|m|iː|h|aɪ|_|ˈ|tʃ|iː|k|s|ɛ|n|t|m|iː|ˌ|h|ɑː|j|iː}}；{{bd|1934年|9月29日|2021年|10月20日|catIdx=Csíkszentmihályi}}<ref>[https://forbes.hu/uzlet/meghalt-csikszentmihalyi-mihaly-a-flow-elmelet-atyja/ Meghalt Csíkszentmihályi Mihály, a flow elmélet atyja] {{Wayback|url=https://forbes.hu/uzlet/meghalt-csikszentmihalyi-mihaly-a-flow-elmelet-atyja/ |date=20211021062419 }} {{in lang|hu}}</ref>），是一位[[匈牙利裔|匈牙利裔]][[美國|美國]][[心理學家|心理學家]]。<ref>{{cite news|last1=O'Keefe|first1=Paul A.|title=Liking Work Really Matters|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/09/07/opinion/sunday/go-with-the-flow.html?_r=0|newspaper=The New York Times|date=2014-09-04|access-date=2015-10-30|archive-date=2021-04-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210416004720/https://www.nytimes.com/2014/09/07/opinion/sunday/go-with-the-flow.html?_r=0|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Csikszentmihalyi|first1=Mihaly|title=Flow: the psychology of optimal experience|url=https://archive.org/details/flowpsychologyof00csik|url-access=registration|date=1990|publisher=Harper & Row|location=New York|isbn=9780060162535|edition=1st}}</ref> 奇克森特米哈伊·米哈伊創立了[[心流|心流]]的[[正向心理學|正向心理學]]概念，這是一種高度集中的，有利於生產力的精神狀態。奇克森特米哈伊·米哈伊是[[克萊蒙研究大學|克萊蒙研究大學]]傑出的[[心理學|心理學]]和[[管理學|管理學]]教授，亦曾是[[芝加哥大學|芝加哥大學]][[心理學|心理學]]系和[[森林湖學院|森林湖學院]][[社會學|社會學]]與[[人類學系|人類學系]]系主任。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cgu.edu/people/mihaly-csikszentmihalyi/|title=Mihaly Csikszentmihalyi|publisher=Claremont Graduate University|access-date=2017-03-02|archive-date=2021-04-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210415204250/https://www.cgu.edu/people/mihaly-csikszentmihalyi/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==早年生活==
奇克森特米哈伊·米哈伊於1934年9月29日在[[里耶卡|里耶卡]]出生，當時是[[意大利王國_(1861年－1946年)|意大利王國]]的一部分。<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://www.lionsroar.com/the-man-who-found-the-flow/|title=The Man Who Found the Flow|last=Cooper|first=Andrew|date=1998-09-01|work=Lion's Roar|access-date=2018-05-06|language=en-US|archive-date=2021-04-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210415195014/https://www.lionsroar.com/the-man-who-found-the-flow/|dead-url=no}}</ref>他的姓氏來自[[特兰西瓦尼亚|特兰西瓦尼亚]]的村莊[[米赫伊萊尼鄉_(哈爾吉塔縣)|奇克森特米哈伊]]。<ref>{{Cite book|url = https://books.google.com/books?id=TL4_BAAAQBAJ&lpg=PA129&pg=PA129|title = Applications of Flow in Human Development and Education: The Collected Works of Mihaly Csikszentmihalyi|isbn = 9789401790949|last1 = Csikszentmihalyi|first1 = Mihaly|date = 2014-08-08|access-date = 2021-03-02|archive-date = 2021-04-15|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210415195044/https://books.google.com/books?id=TL4_BAAAQBAJ&lpg=PA129&pg=PA129|dead-url = no}}</ref> <ref name=":0" />奇克森特米哈伊是[[匈牙利|匈牙利]]駐菲烏姆領事館職業外交官的三兒子。他的兩個同父異母的兄弟在奇克森特米哈伊很小的時候就死了。其中一名兄弟是工程專業的學生，在[[布達佩斯|布達佩斯]]的圍困中被殺，另一名兄弟是被[[蘇聯|蘇聯]]送往[[西伯利亞|西伯利亞]]的勞改營中去世。<ref name=":1">{{Cite journal|last=Kawamura|first=Kristine Marin|date=2014|title=Kristine Marin Kawamura, PhD interviews Mihaly Csikszentmihalyi, PhD|journal=Cross Cultural Management|publisher=Emerald Group Publishing Limited|volume=21|issue=4|doi=10.1108/CCM-08-2014-0094}}</ref> 

第二次世界大戰後不久，奇克森特米哈伊的父親被任命為[[匈牙利|匈牙利]]駐意大利大使，將全家遷至[[羅馬|羅馬]]。<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":2">{{Cite web|url=http://tsl.news/articles/2015/2/6/news/5935-q-and-a-cgu-professor-mihaly-csikszentmihalyi-receives-hungarian-national-award|title=Q&A: CGU Professor Mihaly Csikszentmihalyi Receives Hungarian National Award|last=Pontifex|first=Trevor|date=2015-02-06|website=The Student Life|publisher=[[Claremont_Colleges|Claremont Colleges]]|location=[[Claremont,_California|Claremont, California]]|access-date=2018-05-06|archive-date=2018-07-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180718030517/http://tsl.news/articles/2015/2/6/news/5935-q-and-a-cgu-professor-mihaly-csikszentmihalyi-receives-hungarian-national-award|dead-url=yes}}</ref>1949年共產黨人接管匈牙利時，奇克森特米哈伊·米哈伊的父親因不想為該政權工作而辭職，故匈牙利共產黨政權驅逐了他們一家，並剝奪了他們的匈牙利國籍。為了謀生，奇克森特米哈伊·米哈伊的父親在羅馬開了一家餐館，而奇克森特米哈伊輟學以幫助家庭增加收入。這時，年輕的奇克森特米哈伊·米哈伊當時在瑞士旅行，看到[[卡爾·榮格|卡爾·榮格]]講述了人類目擊外來飛行物體的心理影響。<ref name=":0" />奇克森特米哈伊在22歲時移民到美國，並在[[芝加哥大學|芝加哥大學]]學習期間獲得了文學學士學位，及後在1959年獲得博士學位。然後，他在[[森林湖學院|森林湖學院]]任教，然後在1969年成為[[芝加哥大學|芝加哥大學]]的教授。<ref name=":1" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cgu.edu/pages/4751.asp|title=Mihaly Csikszentmihalyi|publisher=Claremont Graduate University, Division of Behavorial and Organizational Sciences|location=Claremont, Calif.|access-date=2014-03-03|quote=B.A., University of Chicago, 1960|archive-date=2020-11-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201117224820/https://www.cgu.edu/pages/4751.asp|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==工作==

奇克森特米哈伊大多研究[[幸福|幸福]]及[[創造力|創造力]]方面的工作，但最主力的研究是[[心流|心流]]概念。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.brainchannels.com/thinker/mihaly.html |title=Thinker of the Year Award |access-date=2021-03-02 |archive-date=2020-11-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201105231935/http://www.brainchannels.com/thinker/mihaly.html |dead-url=no }}</ref> 他是許多書籍的作者，並撰寫了290餘篇文章或書籍章節。 [[美國心理學會|美國心理學會]]前主席[[馬丁·賽里格曼|馬丁·賽里格曼]]稱奇克森特米哈伊·米哈伊是世界領先的[[正向心理學|正向心理學]]研究者。 奇克森特米哈伊·米哈伊曾經說過：“壓迫不是通往美德的途徑。當人們因為恐懼而束縛自己時，生活必定會減少。只有通過自由選擇的紀律，才能享受生活，並將生活保持在理性範圍之內。” <ref name="focusdep">{{cite web|url=http://www.focusdep.com/quotes/topics/virtue/start/0/ |title=Virtue Quotes & Quotations |publisher=focusdep.com |access-date=2014-01-19 |dead-url=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131111201415/http://focusdep.com/quotes/topics/virtue/start/0/ |archive-date=2013-11-11 }}</ref> 他的著作對[[正向心理學|正向心理學]]有十分大的影響力，並被廣泛引用。<ref>Nigel King & Neil Anderson (2002). ''Managing Innovation and Change''. Cengage Learning EMEA. p. 82. ({{ISBN|1861527837}})</ref>

===心流===

{{main|心流理論}}

他在著作《心流：最佳體驗的心理學》概述了心流理論：心流是一種專注或完全沉浸在当下活动和事情的狀態。沉浸在心流狀態的人会感受到涅磐般的快樂。<ref name="flowthepsychologyofoptimalexperience">Csikszentmihalyi, M. (1990). ''Flow: The Psychology of Optimal Experience''. New York: Harper and Row. p. 15 {{ISBN|0-06-092043-2}}</ref>心流时的內在動機的达到最佳，让人完全沉浸在他們正在做的事情中。<ref name=flow/>每個人都有过心流体验，会在感到全神貫注、充满成就感的同时，忽略世俗的需求（時間、食物、自我等）。<ref name=flow>{{cite book|last1=Csikszentmihalyi|first1=Mihaly|title=Flow: The Psychology of Optimal Experience|url=https://archive.org/details/flowpsychologyop00csik_200|date=1990|publisher=Harper Perennial Modern Classics|page=[https://archive.org/details/flowpsychologyop00csik_200/page/n38 27]}}</ref>

在接受《連線》雜誌採訪時，他形容当人进入心流状态时，自我和時間的感觉会暂时消失。動作和想法接连不断的出现，如同演奏爵士樂，最大程度把自己融入其中。”<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.wired.com/wired/archive/4.09/czik_pr.html |title=Geirland, John (1996). "Go With The Flow". ''Wired'', September, Issue 4.09. |access-date=2022-03-11 |archive-date=2021-10-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211021174332/https://www.wired.com/1996/09/czik/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>具有內在自我驅動性格特質的人謙遜，有毅力和充滿好奇心，<ref>Csikszentmihalyi, M. & Nakamura, J. (2011). Positive psychology: Where did it come from, where is it going? In K. M. Sheldon, T. B. Kashdan, & M. F. Steger (Eds.), ''Designing positive psychology'' (pp. 2–9). New York: Oxford University Press.</ref>他們樂於按內在動因行事而不屑於追求實現外部目標，<ref>Car, A. ''Positive psychology. The Science of happiness and human strengths''. Hove, 2004. </ref>他們能夠從常人無法忍受的事情上獲得樂趣。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.scarymommy.com/complex-person/|title=What Does It Mean To Be A Complex Person? 7 Traits To Look For|date=3 October 2021|publisher=Scary Mommy|accessdate=21 October 2021|archive-date=2021-10-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211021174337/https://www.scarymommy.com/complex-person/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

心流的九個組成部分：平衡任務難度和能力，行為和注意力的融合，清晰的目標，清楚的即時反饋，注意力投射在手邊的任務，微妙的自我控制，時間的時間，自我意識的消失，內在驅動力的體驗。<ref name="flowatwork">{{cite journal | last1 = Fullagar | first1 = Clive J. | last2 = Kelloway | first2 = E. Kevin | year = 2009 | title = Flow at work: an experience sampling approach | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-occupational-and-organizational-psychology_2009-09_82_3/page/595 | journal = Journal of Occupational and Organizational Psychology | volume = 82 | issue = 3| pages = 595–615 | doi=10.1348/096317908x357903}}</ref>實現心流要求任務難度和自身能力水平必須高度匹配，如果任務太容易或太難，心流不會出現。<ref name=BBF>{{cite web|url=https://www.bendbulletin.com/explore/the-elasticity-of-time-in-flow-state/article_dd142446-1be5-11ec-ae4a-33384e32b465.html|title=The elasticity of time in 'flow state'|date=24 September 2021|publisher=Bend Bulletin|access-date=2022-03-11|archive-date=2021-09-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210924112027/https://www.bendbulletin.com/explore/the-elasticity-of-time-in-flow-state/article_dd142446-1be5-11ec-ae4a-33384e32b465.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

===動機===

他晚期主要研究驅使們面對挑戰，追求幸福感的機制和因素。<ref name=mota/> <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog/the-athletes-way/202110/why-team-flow-is-unique-brain-state|title=Why Team Flow Is a Unique Brain State|publisher=Psychology Today|accessdate=21 October 2021|archive-date=2021-10-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211021174332/https://www.psychologytoday.com/us/blog/the-athletes-way/202110/why-team-flow-is-unique-brain-state|dead-url=no}}</ref> 他的研究發現自我驅動的人，能在追求有挑戰性的目標中獲得更大的幸福感。<ref name=mota>{{cite journal|last=Abuhamdeh|first=Sami|author2=Csikszentmihalyi, Mihaly|title=The importance of challenge for the enjoyment of intrinsically motivated, goal-directed activities.|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_personality-and-social-psychology-bulletin_2012-03_38_3/page/317|journal=Personality and Social Psychology Bulletin|year=2012|volume=38|issue=3|pmid=22067510|doi=10.1177/0146167211427147|pages=317–30|s2cid=11916899}}</ref>面對挑戰的時候，內在動機是人們優化體驗，增強積極情緒和獲得幸福感的催化劑。<ref name=Worko/>

他的晚期研究結果揭示了一種新的性格特質，他稱之為任務取向，特點是：成就感，耐力，認知結構，指令，行動和低衝動。<ref name=Worko/> 與其他影響因素相比，學生的任務取向水平可以更好地預測其長期的學業成就。<ref name=Worko>{{cite journal|last=Wong|first=Maria|author2=Mihaly Csikszentmihalyi|title=Motivation and academic achievement: The effects of personality traits and the quality of experience|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-personality_1991-09_59_3/page/539|journal=Journal of Personality|year=1991|volume=59|issue=3|doi=10.1111/j.1467-6494.1991.tb00259.x|pages=539–574|pmid=1960642}}</ref>

